======================================================================
		FOR LINUX AND WINDOWS ONLY				
======================================================================
1) 	Note: virtual environment creation is optional, you can 	
	start from step 3 and it won't create problems;		
									
	Create a Virtual Environment using conda: 			
									
	conda create -n <virtual_environment_name>			
									
2) 	Activate your newly created virtual environment:		
									
	conda activate <virtual_environment_name>			
									
3) 	Install all the packages mentioned in requirements.txt 	
	using the command below (use pip3 if needed):			
									
	pip install -r requirements.txt				
									
4) 	Run make_dataset.py with the command:				
									
	python make_dataset.py -o dataset-[firstname-lastname]	
									
	eg: python make_dataset.py -o dataset-shweta-prasad		
======================================================================
									
======================================================================

